text: Skara is a town in the county of Västra Götaland in Sweden. It is the seat of Skara Municipality. Skara is the home of Skara Cathedral, and Swedish record label Mariann Grammofon as well. Founding dates back to 988 (traditional date). From 1634 and until 1660, Skara was the seat of Skaraborg County. == Famous people == *Bert Karlsson, Swedish record label manager and politician == References == ==Other websites== Category:Settlements in Vastra Gotaland County
